The paper deals with reinforcement learning algorithms and policy optimization, which are core topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of value functions and policy gradients also suggests a focus on optimization and control, which are common themes in robotics and systems engineering. The paper also introduces a novel fingerprinting mechanism for policy representation, which could be relevant to computer vision and image processing applications. Overall, the paper's interdisciplinary nature and focus on machine learning and optimization make cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.CV the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories.
